      "title": "UNIT 55 — Jumping Frog",
      "text": "Mark Twain once wrote a story called “The Celebrated Jumping Frog of Calaveras County.” The story became very famous. It gave the people who really lived in Calaveras County a great idea—to have a frog-jumping contest. The contest has been held every year since 1928 at Angel's Camp, Calaveras County, California. Fifty-one frogs competed in the first contest. The winning frog jumped 3 feet, 4 inches. In a more recent contest, Rosie the Ribeter won with a jump of 21 feet, 5¾ inches. Are the frogs stronger than they used to be, or have they been getting more practice? Whatever the reason, the frogs are jumping better than ever.",
